cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper discusses the relationship between neural networks and natural language grammar, and how theoretical insights can help explain neural computation. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the types of computation that neural networks can perform and characterizes the classes of languages acceptable by various types of neural networks. 
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper focuses on neural networks and their computational capabilities. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the theoretical insights that can help interpret and understand neural networks. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the memory and computational capabilities of neural networks, which can be relevant to control systems.
